SUMMARY:Catering to the Car: A Retro Road Trip Down Petaluma’s Main Stre
 et
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T230000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T000000Z
UID:76e66fe17c182ef67a001020ac945f86@petalumaartscenter.org
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/66
 c6495e2b6d0959e53eb16c/1770863786834-RE4IF8MZ428N39HY6S3W/Hollie%27s+616+P
 BS+Credit+Paul+Barber+Collection.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Hollie's 616 PBS Credit Paul Barber Collection Americana Reima
 gined at its best\, this presentation will step into Petaluma’s living h
 istory with historian Katherine Rinehart as she shares stories behind some
  of Petaluma’s classic examples of roadside architecture. Discover how\,
  through adaptive reuse\, these properties reveal the economic and social 
 trends that shaped the city’s past while continuing to serve the needs o
 f today. $15 members\; $20 non-members .fe-block-b77ae59f3137effb1ef9 {mix
 -blend-mode: \; } Get tickets #block-7ac69afb6caf81033ffe {--sqs-block-con
 tent-flex: 0\; } Katherine J. Rinehart is a consulting historian specializ
 ing in house history documentation\, archival organization\, research\, an
 d exhibit development. She holds an MA in History from Sonoma State Univer
 sity and recently founded the Petaluma Signs Project\, &nbsp\;dedicated to
  preserving historic signs that enrich our unique identity.&nbsp\;Previous
 ly\, Katherine managed the Sonoma County History &amp\; Genealogy Library.
  Her current clients include Sonoma State University Library and the Tomal
 es Regional History Center. Katherine is an official Petaluma Good Egg\, a
 n annual honor celebrating individuals who advance the story of the city's
  unique past. She is the author of&nbsp\;Petaluma: A History in Architectu
 re&nbsp\;and co-authored&nbsp\;The Petaluma River: A Sketch Journal and Br
 ief Historical Overview&nbsp\;and the&nbsp\;Petaluma Vintage Signs Guidebo
 ok.&nbsp\; .fe-block-yui_3_17_2_1_1770871281692_3012 {mix-blend-mode: \; }
LOCATION:230 Lakeville Street\, Petaluma\, CA 94952
URL:https://petalumaartscenter.org/events-exhibitions/catering-to-the-car
