UID:event_313759705@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260313T002916Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260315T093000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260315T160000
SUMMARY:FLASH HIKE - Wittenberg\, Sky\, Woodward Valley\, Coast\, Bear Valley Loop
DESCRIPTION:"SONOMA COUNTY OUTDOORS"\nFLASH HIKE - Bear Valley Trailhead at Point Reyes National Seashore.\n\nThis approximately 13-mile hike will depart promptly at 9:40 AM. We will ascend the Mt. Wittenberg Trail (1\,200 feet) to the Sky Trail\, and traverse that to the Woodward Valley Trail. We will descend Woodward Valley to the Coast Trail\, then head south to the giant eucalyptus tree at the Kelham Beach Trailhead (8 miles). After lunch\, we will continue south to the Bear Valley\nTrail and return to the Bear Valley Trailhead (5 miles). Elevation gain is approximately 1\,800 feet\, most of it in the first two miles while ascending Mt. Wittenberg.\n\nBring plenty of water\, a lunch if you wish\, and wear sturdy hiking shoes. This hike offers spectacular vistas of Limantour Beach\, Drake's Estero\, and Point Reyes (if the marine layer allows). There may be a few trees down across the trails...requiring a little scrambling at times.\n\nBinoculars and a camera are suggested! Layers are recommended as this Sunday looks as if it will be partly cloudy with temperatures in the high 60's (offering very comfortable hiking weather).
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/sonoma-county-outdoors/events/313759705/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260312T163248Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260312T163248Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/d/1/d/600_524256125.jpeg
END:VEVENT
