DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260317T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260317T200000
SUMMARY:Tuesday Night Fitness Hike: 5+ Fast Miles\, Downtown Petaluma and Western Hills
DESCRIPTION:"SONOMA COUNTY OUTDOORS"\nWARNING: THE TUESDAY NIGHT FITNESS HIKE IS AN AEROBIC\, FAST-PACED URBAN HIKE! WE TARGET A PACE OF 16-MINUTES PER MILE WITH ONLY BRIEF STOPS (TO REGROUP AS NEEDED). OUR SUMMER ROUTE INCLUDES THE HILLS IN HELEN PUTNAM PARK (740 FT. ELEVATION GAIN)\, AND OUR WINTER ROUTE EXPLORES THE WATER TANKS (690 FT. ELEVATION GAIN). IF YOU FIND YOU ARE HAVING DIFFICULTY KEEPING UP WITH THE LEADERS IN THIS GROUP\, PLEASE USE THE OPT-OUT POINT AT THE FIRST MILE OF THE HIKE! ANOTHER OPTION IS OUR WEDNESDAY NIGHT WALK FOR A MORE MODERATE PACE. THANK YOU FOR HELPING ME KEEP THIS HIKE AN AEROBIC WORKOUT!\n\nNOTE:\nThe Tuesday Night Fitness Hike is posted on the SCO Calendar every week. Steve Tubbs is shown as the host each week but he might\, or might not\, show up to the event. This is\, more often than not\, a small group of regular\, fit walkers who show up on time every Tuesday night to enjoy this rigorous walk. We leave promptly at 6:10 pm from the Kentucky Street entrance to the LanMart Building. So\, if you don't see Steve on the Tuesday night you are there\, you might see him on the next one.\n\nTuesday Night Fitness Hike\, 5+ miles fast paced urban hike:\n\nThis Fitness Hike includes multiple steep uphill portions in Helen Putnam Park (during Daylight Savings Time)\, and at the Petaluma Water Tanks (after Daylight Savings Time ends).\n\nTuesday Night Fitness Hike:\n\n* Warning! This is a FAST hike... a real workout!\n* 5+ miles\n* Meetup time 6:00 pm (We hike at 6:10 sharp)\n* Difficulty is STRENUOUS!\n* 90 minutes\n\nThis is a fast\, evening Fitness Hike that starts downtown outside (on the sidewalk) of the LanMart Building (Brixx Restaurant\, Heebe Jeebe) on Kentucky Street. We head west to Helen Putnam Park (or the Petaluma Water Tanks when DST ends) for some beautiful vistas before returning to our starting point on Kentucky Street. This hike is generally the same route and is focused primarily on fitness.\n\nWHAT TO BRING:\n\n* A good pair of walking/hiking shoes\n* Water (you'll be glad you did)\n* A fun attitude!\n\nWHAT ABOUT THE DARKNESS?\nBring a SMALL flashlight. The sidewalks can be treacherous in west Petaluma\, and you'll want to see those crags\, cracks and upheavals in the concrete. Reflective clothing is also recommended so that vehicles can see you!\n\nSO HOW FAST ARE WE WALKING?\nThe Wednesday Night Walk is about 2.5 mph (22 - 23 minute miles)\nThe Tuesday Night Fitness Hike nearly 3.5 - 4.0 mph (we target a 16 minute mile\, with multiple hills!)\n\nHOW DO YOU PARTICIPATE?\nSign up with Meetup and RSVP Today! This also gets you on our email list to make you aware of upcoming events\, hikes and walks.\n\nWHY DO YOU NEED TO RSVP?\n\nPlease take the time to RSVP YES when you plan on attending an event. It is equally important to keep your RSVP up to date. If you've RSVP'd YES for an event\, we are going to wait for you until the departure time. We leave promptly at 6:10 PM\, so if you arrive late you can join us along the route. We typically hike the same route for each hike\, and our focus is on aerobic exercise.\n\nQUESTIONS?\nEmail me with any questions by using the "Contact Us" link on the left hand side bar of this meetup group page.\n\nHope to see you on a walk or hike soon!\n\nSCO Organizers
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/sonoma-county-outdoors/events/313534125/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260226T025151Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260226T025151Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/f/8/e/600_483032654.jpeg
END:VEVENT
