BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"The Big Easy": "https://bigeasypetaluma.com/event/found-poets-poetry-month-featuring-bernice-espinoza/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:bigeasy
X-SOURCE:The Big Easy
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T153000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T180000
DTSTAMP:20260312T171418
CREATED:20260304T181339Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260304T181339Z
UID:10002566-1775316600-1775325600@bigeasypetaluma.com
SUMMARY:Found Poets POETRY MONTH featuring Bernice Espinoza
DESCRIPTION:Bernice “bere” Espinoza’s performances blend languages\, classes\, joy\, and resistance\, all with the rhythm of real life. She brings everything she has to every performance and this Poetry Month edition is sure to challenge and thrill. \nFound Poets! is about the entertainment of the spirit through performance poetry. From our development program grads to nationally acclaimed headliners\, Found Poets! is a challenging\, committed poetry community dedicated to hosting a good night out.\n(Headliner)\nBernice Espinoza\nBernice “bere” Espinoza is a civil rights activist with a lifelong dedication to social justice. Her poetry has been featured in Palabra by Teatro Campesino and I Love Immigrants at San Jose City College.\nIG: @xochitlacatl_poeticjustice\n(Openers)\nJordan Ranft\nJordan Ranft’s poetry has appeared in Carve Magazine\, Frontier Poetry\, Beaver Magazine\, Bodega\, Moon City Review\, and his chapbook\, Said The Worms (Wrong Publishing\, 2023). In 2015\, he placed third at the National Poetry Slam as a member of Team Berkeley.\nIG: @santarospoetryslam\nJoseph Jason Santiago LaCour\nJoseph Jason Santiago LaCour is a Poet\, Artist and Emcee living in Santa Cruz. A parent of grown girls\, he has true love in his life and he wants to share his art\, his heart\, with you.\nIG: @josephjasonsantiagolacour\nN’Game’ Gray\nN’gamè is a native of Sonoma County and the Founder/Executive Director of NuBridges Youth Collaborative. She has a proclivity & love for Poetry\, in all its forms.\nIG: @sunflower_soul_ngame\nHosted by Josh Windmiller + Original Giotis!
URL:https://bigeasypetaluma.com/event/found-poets-poetry-month-featuring-bernice-espinoza/
LOCATION:The Big Easy\, 128 American Alley\, Petaluma\, CA\, 94952\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://bigeasypetaluma.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/APR-26-Web.png
END:VEVENT
