BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Meetup: Rebel Craft Collective": "https://www.meetup.com/the-rebel-craft-collective/events/313260344/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:meetup_rebel_craft
X-SOURCE:Meetup: Rebel Craft Collective
UID:event_313260344@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260313T002913Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260423T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260423T193000
SUMMARY:Happy Hour Crafts
DESCRIPTION:The Rebel Craft Collective\nWine + tasty snacks + your latest project and a friendly group of likeminded crafters... what better way to unwind? Come join us!\n\nThis is a relaxed\, drop-in-friendly event. Come when you can\, leave when you must. Newcomers and occasional-comers are always welcome!\n\n**What do we mean by “crafts”?**\nWhatever “craft” means to you! And whatever is portable enough to bring to a wine bar. Knitting\, crochet\, and other fiber arts are most common\, but we have also warmly welcomed people who sketch\, color\, embroider\, bead\, and more. If your craft isn’t portable\, we will happily ooh and aah over photos of your work-in-progress\, or chat about your plans for your next project.\n\n**Health & Safety**\nMasks are very welcome\, and nobody will pressure you to eat or drink. If the weather is nice\, we will try to sit outside. If you aren’t eating/drinking during the event\, please consider ordering some of La Dolce Vita’s delicious food to-go\, in order to help support our gracious\, long-time venue.\n\n**Parking**\nParking in downtown Petaluma is free\, but street parking has a strictly enforced 2 hour limit until 6pm. To park for longer\, try the nearest garage:\n\n* The Second Street Garage entrance is located on C Street between First and Second Streets. It's all day parking on every level and a short walk to La Dolce Vita.\n\n**Ages**\nIt's a wine bar\, so this event is for adult crafters (though you're certainly not required to drink wine!). We’re okay with babes-in-arms if you are\, but this is not the right setting for wee crafters who are moving about on their own.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/the-rebel-craft-collective/events/313260344/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260208T041752Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260208T041752Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/a/2/b/3/600_527801651.jpeg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Polly Klaas Community Theater": "https://www.pollyklaastheater.org/event/petaluma-safety-wellbeing-series-social-media-safety-crisis-prevention/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:polly_klaas
X-SOURCE:Polly Klaas Community Theater
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260423T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260423T193000
DTSTAMP:20260312T172921
CREATED:20260227T232041Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260227T232803Z
UID:10000268-1776967200-1776972600@www.pollyklaastheater.org
SUMMARY:Petaluma Safety & Wellbeing Series: Social Media Safety & Crisis Prevention
DESCRIPTION:Join us at 6pm for a FREE dinner from Jersey Mike's Subs\, and learn more about these vital resources! \nSocial Media Safety director\, Lyn Romstad\, will be teaming up with Mario Castillo\, a Community Outreach Education Coordinator with Buckelew’s 988 Suicide Prevention\, for a public presentation at the Theater on April 23! This is the next of PKF’s ongoing Petaluma Community Wellbeing Series presentations in collaboration with other subject matter expert organizations to bring you a free resource to promote safety\, health\, and wellbeing in our community.
URL:https://www.pollyklaastheater.org/event/petaluma-safety-wellbeing-series-social-media-safety-crisis-prevention/
LOCATION:Polly Klaas Community Theater\, 417 Western Avenue\, Petaluma\, CA\, 94952\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://www.pollyklaastheater.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/SMSE-4.23-ad-03-e1772234857847.png
ORGANIZER;CN="Polly Klaas Community Theater":MAILTO:events@pollyklaas.org
END:VEVENT
